cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses a deep reinforcement learning algorithm for high-fidelity imitation learning, which involves learning policies for diverse novel skills and solving tasks more efficiently than the demonstrators. This falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on using vision as input and learning from sparse rewards, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
